# Machinecraft Business Rules

These are hard constraints. Violating any of these in code, prompts, or data will cause Ira to give wrong answers to customers.

## Machine Series Routing

| Condition | Route To | NEVER Route To |
|-----------|----------|----------------|
| Thickness <= 1.5mm | AM series | PF1-C/X |
| Thickness > 1.5mm | PF1-C or PF1-X | AM series |
| TPO + grain retention + Class-A | IMG series | PF1 alone |
| Bathtubs / shower trays | PF2 | PF1, AM |
| Thin + thick on same machine | TWO machines needed | "One machine for both" |

## Pricing

- Every price MUST include "subject to configuration and current pricing"
- PF1-X prices are in `data/brain/machine_specs.json` — use exact numbers, not "PF1-C + 50-60%"
- EUR/USD conversions are indicative (1 EUR ~ 90-92 INR, 1 USD ~ 83-84 INR)
- The full price table is in `tool_orchestrator.py` system prompt — keep it in sync with `machine_specs.json`

## Custom Sizing

Machinecraft can ALWAYS build any size. Never say "we don't make that size." Offer either:
1. The next larger standard model
2. A custom build at exact dimensions (price quoted separately)

Reference: Dutch Tides ordered 6400x1900mm (largest in Europe).

## Lead Time

ALWAYS 12-16 weeks from order confirmation. Never promise faster. Never match a competitor's claimed delivery.

## Closed Customers

Batelaan Kunststoffen (Netherlands) is SHUT DOWN. Never suggest outreach.

## Product Lines

Machinecraft's lines are: PF1, PF2, AM, IMG, FCS, ATF, UNO, DUO. There is NO PF3 series. If a model doesn't exist, say so — never fabricate specs.
